jnxL2cpFeaturesMIB.name: jnxL2cpFeaturesMIB

revisions.description: Modifying max access for LacpTimeOut trap objects.

jnxL2cpFeaturesMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Technical Assistance Center Juniper Networks, Inc. 1194 N. Mathilda Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 E-mail: support@juniper.net
jnxL2cpFeaturesMIB.description: This mib module is for Juniper Networks Proprietory Layer 2 control protocol (L2CP) features

jnxDot1dStpPortProtectTable.name: jnxDot1dStpPortProtectTable
jnxDot1dStpPortProtectTable.description: Defines the jnxDot1dStp Port Table for providing enterprise specific extensions for Root Protect and Loop Protect to the corresponding dot1dStpPortTable entry.

jnxDot1dStpPortProtectEntry.name: jnxDot1dStpPortProtectEntry
jnxDot1dStpPortProtectEntry.description: Defines an entry in the jnxDot1dStpPortProtectTable. This essentially augments the dot1dStpPortTable with additional objects.

jnxDot1dStpPortRootProtectEnabled.name: jnxDot1dStpPortRootProtectEnabled
jnxDot1dStpPortRootProtectEnabled.description: A Boolean value set by management indicating whether Root protect functionality is enabled on the port. If TRUE causes the Port not to be selected as Root Port, even it has the best spanning tree priority vector. This parameter should be FALSE by default.

jnxDot1dStpPortRootProtectState.name: jnxDot1dStpPortRootProtectState
jnxDot1dStpPortRootProtectState.description: Indicates whether the port was prevented from being a root port. This parameter will always return 'no-error (0)' if jnxDot1dStpPortRootProtectEnabled is FALSE.

jnxDot1dStpPortLoopProtectEnabled.name: jnxDot1dStpPortLoopProtectEnabled
jnxDot1dStpPortLoopProtectEnabled.description: A Boolean value set by management indicating whether Loop protect functionality is enabled on the port. If TRUE causes the Port not to be selected as Designated Port when the received superior BPDU is aged out. This parameter should be FALSE by default.

jnxDot1dStpPortLoopProtectState.name: jnxDot1dStpPortLoopProtectState
jnxDot1dStpPortLoopProtectState.description: Indicates whether a potential Loop was prevented on the port This parameter will always return 'no-error (0)' if jnxDot1dStpPortLoopProtectEnabled is FALSE.

jnxL2cpBpduProtectPortTable.name: jnxL2cpBpduProtectPortTable
jnxL2cpBpduProtectPortTable.description: Defines a Port Table for BPDU Protect information. This contains only those ports on which BPDU Protect can be configured.

jnxL2cpBpduProtectPortEntry.name: jnxL2cpBpduProtectPortEntry
jnxL2cpBpduProtectPortEntry.description: Defines an entry in the jnxL2cpBpduProtectPortTable. A list containing BPDU Protect information for each Port.

jnxL2cpBpduProtectPortEnabled.name: jnxL2cpBpduProtectPortEnabled
jnxL2cpBpduProtectPortEnabled.description: A Boolean value set by management indicating whether BPDU protect functionality is enabled on the port. If TRUE causes the Port to be disabled (link down) upon receipt of a BPDU. This parameter should be FALSE by default.

jnxL2cpPortBpduError.name: jnxL2cpPortBpduError
jnxL2cpPortBpduError.description: Indicates whether a BPDU was received on the port. This parameter will always return 'no-error (0)' if jnxL2cpBpduProtectPortEnabled is FALSE.

jnxL2cpBpduProtectDisableTimeout.name: jnxL2cpBpduProtectDisableTimeout
jnxL2cpBpduProtectDisableTimeout.description: Returns the value of time (in seconds) after which a port on which BPDU error was detected will be re-enabled. A returned value of 0 indicates that port will not be re-enabled automatically.

jnxPortRootProtectStateChangeTrap.name: jnxPortRootProtectStateChangeTrap
jnxPortRootProtectStateChangeTrap.description: Generated when the ports Root-protect state (no-error or root-prevented) changes.

jnxPortLoopProtectStateChangeTrap.name: jnxPortLoopProtectStateChangeTrap
jnxPortLoopProtectStateChangeTrap.description: Generated when the ports Loop-protect state (no-error or loop-prevented) changes.

jnxPortBpduErrorStatusChangeTrap.name: jnxPortBpduErrorStatusChangeTrap
jnxPortBpduErrorStatusChangeTrap.description: Generated when the ports BPDU error state (no-error or detected) changes.

LacpState.name: LacpState
LacpState.description: The Actor and Partner State values from the LACPDU.

dot3adAggPortTimeoutTable.name: dot3adAggPortTimeoutTable
dot3adAggPortTimeoutTable.description: A table that contains Link Aggregation Timeout information about a port that is associated with this device. A row appears in this table for each physical port.

dot3adAggPortTimeoutEntry.name: dot3adAggPortTimeoutEntry
dot3adAggPortTimeoutEntry.description: A list of Link Aggregation Control Protocol timeout information for a port on this device.

dot3adInterfaceName.name: dot3adInterfaceName
dot3adInterfaceName.description: Physical port that is associated with Aggregation Port. This value is read-only.

dot3adOperState.name: dot3adOperState
dot3adOperState.description: A string of 8 bits, corresponding to the current operational values of Actor_State as transmitted by the Actor in LACPDUs. The bit allocations are as defined in 30.7.2.1.20. This attribute value is read-only.

dot3adAggname.name: dot3adAggname
dot3adAggname.description: Aggregation Port where Physical port is associated with. This value is read-only.

dot3adInterfaceTimeout.name: dot3adInterfaceTimeout
dot3adInterfaceTimeout.description: This object represents the time elapsed in seconds since lacp experienced timeout. This value is read-only.
